{
  "texts": [
    "By construction, L u and L d are not independent, since their product yields the CKM matrix:V CKM = L † u L d.The parametric form of L d (and L u) can be determined under the assumption of a minimal breaking of the U(2) 5 symmetry [4].",
    "This corresponds to assuming that the heavy-light mixing in the CKM matrix is induced by a single spurion transforming as a 2 of U(2) q.",
    "Under this natural assumption, one obtains [22] L d ≈    U d 0 ε F V cb ε F V td ε F V ts 1   , U d = c d -s d e iα s d e -iα c d, (2.8)withs d /c d = |V td /V ts | and α d = arg(V * td /V * ts).",
    "This form for L d yields exactly eqs.",
    "(2.5)-(2.6)."
  ]
}